  "text": "Cre or ERT2 Cre animals was reported to be well tolerated in adult animals (Hoshii et al., 2012; Kalaitzidis et al., 2012) . By contrast, inducible deletion of the mTOR kinase in adult mice has recently been reported to result in severe anemia and lethality within 17 days [CITATION_1] . The more dramatic phenotype following mTOR deletion may reflect the role of other mTOR complexes in erythropoiesis or reflect differences in recombination efficiency and selectivity between these experiments. To directly address the role of mTOR during the development of the hematopoietic system, we mated Vav1",
